The program to implement the sequence of FIGS. 6 or 7 runs on a standard gaming machine control processor 31 as illustrated schematically in FIG. 8. This processor forms part of a controller 30 which drives the display screen 11 and receives touch input signals from touch sensors 32 as well as receiving coin input pulses from a coin chute mechanism 33 and driving a coin payout mechanism 34. It will be appreciated that while the flow diagram of FIG. 6 shows a linear program sequence the testing for player selection may be occurring continuously by way of a hardware interrupt subroutine triggered either by a timer or an input detection circuit, in which case the input testing step may occur at any point in the loop. This alternative arrangement is illustrated in the flow diagram of FIG. 7.
